Most of our schools have done this weekly orâ€¦

@Mr_AlmondED @ReBuckEdu @lwilliamsjones what walkthrus are and how theyâ€™re structured etc without being overloaded with new material too. Working on this as a whole school will mean that it gets people talking and using the same language. You can do 5 min catch ups about it in staff meetings/briefings andâ€¦

@Mr_AlmondED @ReBuckEdu @lwilliamsjones is and what it isnâ€™t. Iâ€™ve found that launching the context and rationale first has a more positive impact than just launching a chosen walkthru or cluster first.

@Mr_AlmondED @ReBuckEdu @lwilliamsjones The most important thing for me is to go slow and have a less is more attitude. I reckon going in all guns blazing with instructional coaching and clusters without setting the scene could really turn staff off.
